{"title_page": "Robert Cruickshank (sailor)", "text_new": "{{short description|British sailor|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{MedalTableTop}}\n{{MedalCountry |the {{UK}} }}\n{{MedalSport | [[Sailing]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Barcelona]] | [[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics|Soling]]}}\n{{MedalBottom}}\n'''Robert Cruickshank''' (born 19 February 1963) is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[sailor]]. He won a bronze medal in the [[soling]] class at the [[1992 Summer Olympics]] with [[Lawrie Smith]] and [[Ossie Stewart]].\n{{Footer British Championship Winners in Soling}}\n==References==\n* [https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/cr/robert-cruickshank-1.html Profile] at sports-reference.com\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cruickshank, Robert}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from London]]\n[[Category:British male sailors (sport)]]\n[[Category:Olympic sailors of Great Britain]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medallists for Great Britain]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in sailing]]\n\n\n{{UK-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n{{UK-yachtracing-bio-stub}}\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|British sailor|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{MedalTableTop}}\n{{MedalCountry |the {{UK}} }}\n{{MedalSport | [[Sailing]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Barcelona]] | [[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics|Soling]]}}\n{{MedalBottom}}\n'''Robert Cruickshank''' (born 19 February 1963) is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[sailor]]. He won a bronze medal in the [[soling]] class at the [[1992 Summer Olympics]] with [[Lawrie Smith]] and [[Ossie Stewart]].\n\n==References==\n* [https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/cr/robert-cruickshank-1.html Profile] at sports-reference.com\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cruickshank, Robert}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from London]]\n[[Category:British male sailors (sport)]]\n[[Category:Olympic sailors of Great Britain]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medallists for Great Britain]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in sailing]]\n\n\n{{UK-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n{{UK-yachtracing-bio-stub}}\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n", "name_user": "Dragon Genoa", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Cruickshank_(sailor)"}
{"title_page": "Geir Frig\u00e5rd", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Geir Frig\u00e5rd\n| fullname = Geir Frig\u00e5rd\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1970|11|3|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Vormsund]], Norway\n| height = 1.84 m\n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1 =\n| youthclubs1 = [[Funnefoss/Vormsund IL|Funnefoss/Vormsund]]\n| youthyears2 =\n| youthclubs2 = [[L\u00f8venstad FK|L\u00f8venstad]]\n| years1 = 1989\u20131992\n| clubs1 = [[Lillestr\u00f8m SK|Lillestr\u00f8m]]\n| caps1 = 31\n| goals1 = 9\n| years2 = 1993\u20131994\n| clubs2 = [[Kongsvinger IL|Kongsvinger]]\n| caps2 = 44\n| goals2 = 22\n| years3 = 1995\u20131997\n| clubs3 = [[Lillestr\u00f8m SK|Lillestr\u00f8m]]\n| caps3 = 60\n| goals3 = 22\n| years4 = 1997\u20131998\n| clubs4 = [[LASK Linz]]\n| caps4 = 27\n| goals4 = 23\n| years5 = 1998\u20131999\n| clubs5 = [[Tennis Borussia Berlin]]\n| caps5 = 14\n| goals5 = 5\n| years6 = 1999\u20132000\n| clubs6 = [[CS Sedan Ardennes|CS Sedan]]\n| caps6 = 13\n| goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2000\u20132001\n| clubs7 = [[LASK Linz]]\n| caps7 = 33\n| goals7 = 15\n| years8 = 2001\u20132004\n| clubs8 = [[Lierse S.K.|Lierse]]\n| caps8 = 56\n| goals8 = 10\n| years9 = 2004\u20132005\n| clubs9 = [[Hamarkameratene|Ham-Kam]]\n| caps9 = 44\n| goals9 = 10\n| years10 = 2006\u20132007\n| clubs10 = [[Eidsvold TF|Eidsvold Turn]]\n| caps10 = 17\n| goals10 = 12\n| totalcaps = 339\n| totalgoals = 129\n| nationalyears1 = 1994\n| nationalteam1 = [[Norway national football team|Norway]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 5\n| nationalgoals1 = 1\n}}\n\n'''Geir Frig\u00e5rd''' (born 3 November 1970) is a Norwegian former professional [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Forward (association football)|striker]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/intligen/spanien/liga-bbva/2011-12/hamarkameratene-2282/22688/spieler_geir-frigard.html | title = Frigard, Geir | language = German | publisher = kicker.de | accessdate = 5 February 2012}}</ref> He played five times for the national team, scoring one goal. In 1997\u201398, he was top scorer in the [[Austrian Bundesliga]]. He retired from playing in 2007.\n\n==Club career==\n{{Empty section|date=January 2011}}\n\nFrig\u00e5rd was born in [[Vormsund]].\n\n==International career==\nFrig\u00e5rd got his debut in a friendly on 15 January 1994 against [[United States men's national soccer team|USA]] which they lost 2\u20131. He scored his first and only goal in a 1\u20130 win on 7 September 1994 in a [[UEFA Euro 1996]] qualification match against [[Belarus national football team|Belarus]].\n\n==Career statistics==\n===International goals===\n:Source:<ref>[http://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=6307 Player profile] at eu-football.info</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 7 September 1994 || [[Ullevaal Stadion]], [[Oslo]], Norway || {{fb|BLR|1991}} || 1\u20130 || Win || [[UEFA Euro 1996 qualifying]]\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n* [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga]] top scorer: 1998\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Austrian Football Bundesliga top scorers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Frigard, Geir}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Nes, Akershus]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Norwegian footballers]]\n[[Category:Norway international footballers]]\n[[Category:Lillestr\u00f8m SK players]]\n[[Category:Kongsvinger IL Toppfotball players]]\n[[Category:LASK Linz players]]\n[[Category:Tennis Borussia Berlin players]]\n[[Category:CS Sedan Ardennes players]]\n[[Category:Lierse S.K. players]]\n[[Category:Hamarkameratene players]]\n[[Category:Ligue 1 players]]\n[[Category:Eliteserien players]]\n[[Category:Belgian First Division A players]]\n[[Category:Austrian Football Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:2. Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Norwegian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Austria]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Germany]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in France]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Belgium]]\n[[Category:Norwegian expatriate sportspeople in Austria]]\n[[Category:Norwegian expatriate sportspeople in Germany]]\n[[Category:Norwegian expatriate sportspeople in Belgium]]\n[[Category:Norwegian expatriate sportspeople in France]]\n\n{{Norway-footy-forward-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Geir Frig\u00e5rd\n| fullname = Geir Frig\u00e5rd\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1970|11|3|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Vormsund]], Norway\n| height = 1.84 m\n| position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| youthyears1 =\n| youthclubs1 = [[Funnefoss/Vormsund IL|Funnefoss/Vormsund]]\n| youthyears2 =\n| youthclubs2 = [[L\u00f8venstad FK|L\u00f8venstad]]\n| years1 = 1989\u20131992\n| clubs1 = [[Lillestr\u00f8m SK|Lillestr\u00f8m]]\n| caps1 = 31\n| goals1 = 9\n| years2 = 1993\u20131994\n| clubs2 = [[Kongsvinger IL|Kongsvinger]]\n| caps2 = 44\n| goals2 = 22\n| years3 = 1995\u20131997\n| clubs3 = [[Lillestr\u00f8m SK|Lillestr\u00f8m]]\n| caps3 = 60\n| goals3 = 22\n| years4 = 1997\u20131998\n| clubs4 = [[LASK Linz]]\n| caps4 = 27\n| goals4 = 23\n| years5 = 1998\u20131999\n| clubs5 = [[Tennis Borussia Berlin]]\n| caps5 = 14\n| goals5 = 5\n| years6 = 1999\u20132000\n| clubs6 = [[CS Sedan Ardennes|CS Sedan]]\n| caps6 = 13\n| goals6 = 1\n| years7 = 2000\u20132001\n| clubs7 = [[LASK Linz]]\n| caps7 = 33\n| goals7 = 15\n| years8 = 2001\u20132004\n| clubs8 = [[Lierse S.K.|Lierse]]\n| caps8 = 56\n| goals8 = 10\n| years9 = 2004\u20132005\n| clubs9 = [[Hamarkameratene|Ham-Kam]]\n| caps9 = 44\n| goals9 = 10\n| years10 = 2006\u20132007\n| clubs10 = [[Eidsvold TF|Eidsvold Turn]]\n| caps10 = 17\n| goals10 = 12\n| totalcaps = 339\n| totalgoals = 129\n| nationalyears1 = 1994\n| nationalteam1 = [[Norway national football team|Norway]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 5\n| nationalgoals1 = 1\n}}\n\n'''Geir Frig\u00e5rd''' (born 3 November 1970) is a Norwegian former professional [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Forward (association football)|striker]]<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/intligen/spanien/liga-bbva/2011-12/hamarkameratene-2282/22688/spieler_geir-frigard.html | title = Frigard, Geir | language = German | publisher = kicker.de | accessdate = 5 February 2012}}</ref> He played five times for the national team, scoring one goal. In 1997\u201398, he was top scorer in the [[Austrian Bundesliga]]. He retired from playing in 2007.\n\n==Club career==\n{{Empty section|date=January 2011}}\n\nFrig\u00e5rd was born in [[Vormsund]].\n\n==International career==\nFrig\u00e5rd got his debut in a friendly on 15 January 1994 against [[United States men's national soccer team|USA]] which they lost 2\u20131. He scored his first and only goal in a 1\u20130 win on 7 September 1994 in a [[UEFA Euro 1996]] qualification match against [[Belarus national football team|Belarus]].\n\n==Career statistics==\n===International goals===\n:Source:<ref>[http://eu-football.info/_player.php?id=6307 Player profile] at eu-football.info</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! # !! Date !! Venue !! Opponent !! Score !! Result !! Competition\n|-\n| 1. || 7 September 1994 || [[Ullevaal Stadion]], [[Oslo]], Norway || {{fb|BLR|1991}} || 1\u20130 || Win || [[UEFA Euro 1996 qualifying]]\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n* [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga]] top scorer: 1998\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Austrian Football Bundesliga top scorers}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Frigard, Geir}}\n[[Category:1970 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Nes, Akershus]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Norwegian footballers]]\n[[Category:Norway international footballers]]\n[[Category:Lillestr\u00f8m SK players]]\n[[Category:Kongsvinger IL Toppfotball players]]\n[[Category:LASK Linz pl