{"title_page": "City and Guilds College Union", "text_new": "{{short description|Student union at the Imperial College}}\n{{notability|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox Students Union\n|name               =\n|image              =\n|motto              =\n|established        =\n|institution        = [[Imperial College London|Imperial College]] [[Imperial College Faculty of Engineering|Faculty of Engineering]] ''(historically [[City and Guilds College]])''\n|president          =\n|vice president     = Fatima Khan\n|honorary secretary = Leah Redmond\n|treasurer          = Hilliam Tung<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cgcu.net/committee|title=committee :: CGCU}}</ref>\n|location           = [[South Kensington]], [[London]], [[United Kingdom]]\n|members            =\n|affiliated         = Constituent union of [[Imperial College Union]] \n|colours           = {{scarf|start}}{{cells|6|maroon}}{{cells|3|white}}{{cells|4|maroon}}{{cells|3|white}}{{cells|6|maroon}}{{scarf|end}}\n|mascot            = Bolt and Spanner, Boanerges, Derrick<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cgcu.net/mascots.html|title=mascots :: CGCU}}</ref>\n|homepage           = [https://cgcu.net cgcu.net] \n}}\nThe '''City and Guilds College Union''' represents students who are undertaking courses from the departments of Aeronautical, Chemical, Civil, Design, Electrical, and Mechanical Engineering, and Computing courses at the college. Other students within the faculty are represented by the [[Royal School of Mines#RSM Student.27s Union|Royal School of Mines Student's Union]]. This follows the traditional constituent colleges that formed Imperial in the early 20th century. The City and Guilds Union's name derives from the original City and Guilds College from which the faculty was formed. The union hosts an annual welcome dinner, and members of the union are traditionally known as Guildsmen and Guildswomen.<ref>{{cite news|work=Felix|title=Keeping up with the Engineers|first1=Lejon|last1=Chua|first2=Carol Ann|last2=Cheah|url=http://felixonline.co.uk/articles/2013-11-5-keeping-up-with-the-engineers/}}</ref> The student's union brings together the 8 departmental societies, and organises events throughout the year, and to welcome new students.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cgcu.net/events.html|title=events :: CGCU}}</ref> \n\nThe union has a traditional rivalry with the [[Royal College of Science Union]], against which it engaged in traditional food fights, and has a chant known as the Boomerlaka.<ref name=hg>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2BpqDQAAQBAJ&|title=The History of Imperial College London, 1907-2007|author=Hannah Gay|date=2007|publisher=World Scientific|isbn=9781860947087|pages=441,457}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imperial.ac.uk/centenary/memories/Morphy.shtml|access-date=30 August 2018|title=Memories, Bob Schroter}}</ref> Its mascots include Boanger, nicknamed \"Bo\", a 1902 [[James & Browne]] which competes in the [[London to Brighton Veteran Car Run]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.classicandsportscar.com/news/classic-car-events/students-to-continue-80-year-tradition-on-the-brighton-run|title=Students to continue 80-year tradition on the Brighton Run|first=James|last=Elliott|date=4 Oct 2013|website=classicandsportscar.com|publisher=Classic & Sports Car}}</ref> The car is run by the union's Motor Club, with the car having been acquired the union for \u00a340 in 1934.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/education/3347199/Wheeling-in-the-years.html|title=Wheeling in the years|first=Ali|last=Watkinson|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|date=27 Nov 2004}}</ref> The union has in the past also organised a tricycle record attempt around the coast of Britain raising money for coastal lifeguards, as well as raft races on the Serpentine and tugs of war in the 1960s with other constituent unions.<ref name=hg /> There remain constant attempts by each union to steal the mascots of the others.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imperialcollegeunion.org/your-union/how-were-run/committees/16-17/Union_Council/file/4368|access-date=30 August 2018|title=Mascotry, A New Policy for Constituent Unions}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://felixonline.co.uk/articles/2016-12-9-keep-your-hands-off-our-mascots/|title=Keep your hands off our mascots|date=9 December 2016|author=Felix Editor|author2=Lef Apostolakis|work=[[Felix (newspaper)|Felix]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Extenal Links ==\n[https://cgcu.net Official Website]\n\n{{ImperialCollege-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Clubs and societies of Imperial College London]]\n[[Category:Imperial College Faculty of Engineering]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Student union at the Imperial College}}\n{{notability|date=April 2020}}\n\n{{Infobox Students Union\n|name               =\n|image              =\n|motto              =\n|established        =\n|institution        = [[Imperial College London|Imperial College]] [[Imperial College Faculty of Engineering|Faculty of Engineering]] ''(historically [[City and Guilds College]])''\n|president          =\n|vice president     = Fatima Khan\n|honorary secretary = Leah Redmond\n|treasurer          = Hilliam Tung<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cgcu.net/committee|title=committee :: CGCU}}</ref>\n|location           = [[South Kensington]], [[London]], [[United Kingdom]]\n|members            =\n|affiliated         = Constituent Union of [[Imperial College Union]] \n|colours           = {{scarf|start}}{{cells|6|maroon}}{{cells|3|white}}{{cells|4|maroon}}{{cells|3|white}}{{cells|6|maroon}}{{scarf|end}}\n|mascot            = Bolt and Spanner, Boanerges, Derrick<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cgcu.net/mascots.html|title=mascots :: CGCU}}</ref>\n|homepage           = [https://cgcu.net cgcu.net] \n}}\nThe '''City and Guilds College Union''' represents students who are undertaking courses from the departments of Aeronautical, Chemical, Civil, Design, Electrical, and Mechanical Engineering, and Computing courses at the college. Other students within the faculty are represented by the [[Royal School of Mines#RSM Student.27s Union|Royal School of Mines Student's Union]]. This follows the traditional constituent colleges that formed Imperial in the early 20th century. The City and Guilds Union's name derives from the original City and Guilds College from which the faculty was formed. The union hosts an annual welcome dinner, and members of the union are traditionally known as Guildsmen and Guildswomen.<ref>{{cite news|work=Felix|title=Keeping up with the Engineers|first1=Lejon|last1=Chua|first2=Carol Ann|last2=Cheah|url=http://felixonline.co.uk/articles/2013-11-5-keeping-up-with-the-engineers/}}</ref> The student's union brings together the 8 departmental societies, and organises events throughout the year, and to welcome new students.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://cgcu.net/events.html|title=events :: CGCU}}</ref> \n\nThe union has a traditional rivalry with the [[Royal College of Science Union]], against which it engaged in traditional food fights, and has a chant known as the Boomerlaka.<ref name=hg>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=2BpqDQAAQBAJ&|title=The History of Imperial College London, 1907-2007|author=Hannah Gay|date=2007|publisher=World Scientific|isbn=9781860947087|pages=441,457}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imperial.ac.uk/centenary/memories/Morphy.shtml|access-date=30 August 2018|title=Memories, Bob Schroter}}</ref> Its mascots include Boanger, nicknamed \"Bo\", a 1902 [[James & Browne]] which competes in the [[London to Brighton Veteran Car Run]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.classicandsportscar.com/news/classic-car-events/students-to-continue-80-year-tradition-on-the-brighton-run|title=Students to continue 80-year tradition on the Brighton Run|first=James|last=Elliott|date=4 Oct 2013|website=classicandsportscar.com|publisher=Classic & Sports Car}}</ref> The car is run by the union's Motor Club, with the car having been acquired the union for \u00a340 in 1934.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/education/3347199/Wheeling-in-the-years.html|title=Wheeling in the years|first=Ali|last=Watkinson|work=[[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|date=27 Nov 2004}}</ref> The union has in the past also organised a tricycle record attempt around the coast of Britain raising money for coastal lifeguards, as well as raft races on the Serpentine and tugs of war in the 1960s with other constituent unions.<ref name=hg /> There remain constant attempts by each union to steal the mascots of the others.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imperialcollegeunion.org/your-union/how-were-run/committees/16-17/Union_Council/file/4368|access-date=30 August 2018|title=Mascotry, A New Policy for Constituent Unions}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://felixonline.co.uk/articles/2016-12-9-keep-your-hands-off-our-mascots/|title=Keep your hands off our mascots|date=9 December 2016|author=Felix Editor|author2=Lef Apostolakis|work=[[Felix (newspaper)|Felix]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== Extenal Links ==\n[https://cgcu.net Official Website]\n\n{{ImperialCollege-stub}}\n\n[[Category:Clubs and societies of Imperial College London]]\n[[Category:Imperial College Faculty of Engineering]]\n", "name_user": "Shadowssettle", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix caps", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/City_and_Guilds_College_Union"}
{"title_page": "Andy Beadsworth", "text_new": "{{short description|Olympic sailor from Great Britain}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox sailor\n| name           = Andy Beadsworth<ref name=\"Sports-Reference\" />\n| image          = \n| image_size     = \n| caption        = \n| native_name    = \n| birth_name     =  \n| fullname       = Andrew Beadsworth \n| nickname       = \n| nationality    = {{GBR}}\n| birth_date     = {{birth date|1967|4|29|df=y}}\n| birth_place    = [[Nottingham]]\n| death_date     = \n| death_place    = \n| height         = {{convert|1.85|m|ft|abbr=on}}\n| weight         = \n| classes        = [[Soling]]\n| club           = \n| collegeteam    = \n| coach          = \n| medaltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n| updated        = 29 February 2020\n}}\n\n'''Andy Beadsworth''' (born: 28 April 1967 [[Nottingham]]) is a sailor from [[Great Britain]], who represented his country at the [[Sailing at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|1996 Summer Olympics]] in [[Savannah]], [[United States]] as helmsman in the [[Soling]]. With crew members [[Barry Parkin]] and [[Adrian Stead]] they took the 4th place.<ref name=\"OS1996\" /> During the [[Sailing at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|2000 Summer Olympics]] in [[Sydney]], [[Australia]] Andy took 12th place in the [[Soling]] with crew members [[Barry Parkin]] and [[Richard Sydenham]].<ref name=\"OS2000\" />\n{{Footer British Championship Winners in Soling}}\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs =\n  <ref name = Sports-Reference>{{cite web\n                                  |url        = https://web.archive.org/web/20121109043327/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/be/andy-beadsworth-1.html\n                                  |title      = Andy Beadsworth Bio, Stats, and Results \n                                  |publisher  = Sports-Reference.com \n                                  |work       = Olympic Sports \n                                  |accessdate = 29 February 2020