ltemplates = \n| show-medals    = \n| updated        = 29 February 2020\n}}\n\n'''Andy Beadsworth''' (born: 28 April 1967 [[Nottingham]]) is a sailor from [[Great Britain]], who represented his country at the [[Sailing at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|1996 Summer Olympics]] in [[Savannah]], [[United States]] as helmsman in the [[Soling]]. With crew members [[Barry Parkin]] and [[Adrian Stead]] they took the 4th place.<ref name=\"OS1996\" /> During the [[Sailing at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling|2000 Summer Olympics]] in [[Sydney]], [[Australia]] Andy took 12th place in the [[Soling]] with crew members [[Barry Parkin]] and [[Richard Sydenham]].<ref name=\"OS2000\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|refs =\n  <ref name = Sports-Reference>{{cite web\n                                  |url        = https://web.archive.org/web/20121109043327/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/be/andy-beadsworth-1.html\n                                  |title      = Andy Beadsworth Bio, Stats, and Results \n                                  |publisher  = Sports-Reference.com \n                                  |work       = Olympic Sports \n                                  |accessdate = 29 February 2020 \n                                  |url-status = live\n                                  |df=dmy \n                                }}</ref>\n  <ref name = OS1996>{{cite web\n                        | url        = https://digital.la84.org/digital/collection/p17103coll8/id/36188/rec/78\n                        | title      = Official Report of the Centennial Olympic Games, v.3\n                        | year       = 1996\n                        | format     = PDF\n                        | accessdate = 28 February 2020\n                       }}</ref>\n  <ref name = OS2000>{{cite web\n                        | url        = https://digital.la84.org/digital/collection/p17103coll8/id/51224/rec/1\n                        | title      = Sailing. Official Report of