urs==\n===Domestic===\n*''' [[Superleague Greece|Super League]]'''<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.epo.gr/Default.aspx?a_id=25295 |script-title=el:\u039f\u03b9 \u03a0\u03c1\u03c9\u03c4\u03b1\u03b8\u03bb\u03b7\u03c4\u03ad\u03c2 \u0395\u03bb\u03bb\u03ac\u03b4\u03b1\u03c2 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf 1928 \u03bc\u03ad\u03c7\u03c1\u03b9 \u03c3\u03ae\u03bc\u03b5\u03c1\u03b1|publisher=[[Hellenic Football Federation]] epo.gr |language=Greek }}</ref><ref name=\"champ rsssf\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesg/grkchamp.html|title=List of Greece championships|last=K\u00e1rp\u00e1ti|first=Tam\u00e1s|author2=Sch\u00f6ggl, Hans|website=[[RSSSF]]|accessdate=12 April 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"pao trophies\">{{cite web|url=http://www.pao.gr/en/history/trophies/| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160119053111/http://www.pao.gr/en/history/trophies/\n | archivedate=19 January 2016|title=Trophy Room|website=[[Panathinaikos|Pao.gr]]|accessdate=12 April 2012}}</ref><ref name=\"pao uefa\">{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/teamsandplayers/teams/club=50084/profile/index.html|title=Panathinaikos FC profile|website=[[Uefa.com]]|accessdate=12 April 2012}}</ref>\n**'''Winners (20): '''[[Alpha Ethniki|1929\u201330]], [[Alpha Ethniki|1948\u201349]], [[Alpha Ethniki|1952\u201353]], [[Alpha Ethniki 1959-60|1959\u201360]], [[Alpha Ethniki 1960-61|1960\u201361]], [[Alpha Ethniki 1961-62|1961\u201362]], [[1963\u201364 in Greek football|1963\u201364]], [[1964\u201365 in Greek football|1964\u201365]], [[1968\u201369 in Greek football|1968\u201369]], [[1969\u201370 in Greek football|1969\u201370]], [[1971\u201372 in Greek football|1971\u201372]], [[1976\u201377 in Greek football|1976\u201377]], [[1983\u201384 in Greek football|1983\u201384]], [[1985\u201386 in Greek football|1985\u201386]], [[1989\u201390 in Greek football|1989\u201390]], [[1990\u201391 in Greek football|1990\u201391]], [[1994\u201395 in Greek football|1994\u201395]], [[1995\u201396 in Greek football|1995\u201396]], [[2003\u201304 in Greek football|2003\u201304]], [[2009\u201310 Super League Greece|2009\u201310]]\n*''' [[Greek Cup]]'''<ref name=\"pao trophies\"/><ref name=\"pao uefa\"/><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesg/grkcuphist.html |title=Greece&nbsp;\u2013 List of Cup Winners|website=Rsssf.com }}</ref>\n**'''Winners (18):''' [[1939\u201340 Greek Cup|1939\u201340]], [[1947\u201348 Greek Cup|1947\u201348]], [[1954\u201355 Greek Cup|1954\u201355]], [[1966\u201367 Greek Cup|1966\u201367]], [[1968\u201369 Greek Cup|1968\u201369]], [[1976\u201377 Greek Cup|1976\u201377]], [[1981\u201382 Greek Cup|1981\u201382]], [[1983\u201384 Greek Cup|1983\u201384]], [[1985\u201386 Greek Cup|1985\u201386]], [[1987\u201388 Greek Cup|1987\u201388]], [[1988\u201389 Greek Cup|1988\u201389]], [[1990\u201391 Greek Cup|1990\u201391]], [[1992\u201393 Greek Cup|1992\u201393]], [[1993\u201394 Greek Cup|1993\u201394]], [[1994\u201395 Greek Cup|1994\u201395]], [[2003\u201304 Greek Cup|2003\u201304]], [[2009\u201310 Greek Cup|2009\u201310]], [[2013\u201314 Greek Football Cup|2013\u201314]]\n\n===European competitions===\n* '''[[UEFA Champions League]]:'''\n** Runners-up (1): [[1971 European Cup Final|1970\u201371]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/history/season=1970/index.html |title=Cruyff pulls the strings |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111213162802/http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/history/season%3D1970/index.html |archivedate=13 December 2011 |publisher=[[Union of European Football Associations]] (UEFA) |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n** Semi-finals (2): [[1984\u201385 European Cup|1984\u201385]], [[1995\u201396 UEFA Champions League|1995\u201396]]\n** Quarter-finals (2): [[1991\u201392 European Cup|1991\u201392]], [[2001\u201302 UEFA Champions League|2001\u201302]]\n* '''[[UEFA Cup]]:'''\n** Quarter-finals (2): [[1987\u201388 UEFA Cup|1987\u201388]], [[2002\u201303 UEFA Cup|2002\u201303]]\n*''' [[Balkans Cup]]:'''<ref name=\"balkan cup rsssf\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesb/balkan-club.html|title=Balkan Cup|last=Ionescu|first=Romeo|author2=Stokkermans Karel |website=[[RSSSF]]}}</ref>\n** '''Winners (1)''': [[1977 Balkans Cup|1977]]\n\n===Worldwide competitions===\n* '''[[Intercontinental Cup (football)|Intercontinental Cup]]:'''<ref name=\"Intercontinental Cup rsssf\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablest/toyota.html|title=Intercontinental Club Cup|last=Magnani|first=Loris|author2=Stokkermans Karel |website=[[RSSSF]]}}</ref>\n** Runners-up (1): [[1971 Intercontinental Cup|1971]]\n\n===Doubles===\n*'''Winners (8):''' 1968\u201369, 1976\u201377, 1983\u201384, 1985\u201386, 1990\u201391, 1994\u201395, 2003\u201304, 2009\u201310\n\n===Regional===\n*''' [[SEGAS]] and FCA Championship:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesg/grkprehist.html#22|title=Greece - Final Tables 1906-1959|website=Rsssf.com|access-date=18 November 2017}}</ref>\n**'''Winners (6):'''  1909, [[1910\u201311 Panhellenic Championship|1910\u201311]], 1912, 1915, 1921, [[1921\u201322 Panhellenic Championship|1921\u201322]]\n*''' [[SEGAS]] and FCA Cup:\n**'''Winners (2):'''  1909, 1918\n* ''' [[Athens Football Clubs Association#List of Champions|Athens FCA Championship]]:'''<ref name=\"panh rsssf\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesg/grkprehist.html#22|title=Greek final tables 1906\u20131960|last=Mastrogiannopoulos|first=Alexander|website=[[RSSSF]]|access-date=12 April 2012}}</ref>\n**'''Winners (17) (record):''' 1925, 1926, 1927, 1929, 1930, 1931, 1934, 1937, 1939, 1949, 1952, 1953, 1954, 1955, 1956, 1957, 1959\n*''' [[Greek Super Cup]]'''<ref name=\"scup rsssf\">{{cite web|url=http://www.rsssf.com/tablesg/grksupcuphist.html|title=Greece - List of Super Cup and League Cup Finals|website=[[RSSSF]]}}</ref>\n**'''Winners (3):''' 1988, 1993, 1994\n* ''' [[Football Cup of Greater Greece|Greater Greece Cup]]:'''\n**'''Winners (1):''' 1970\n\n==Players==\n===Current squad===\n{{updated|23 January 2020}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pao.gr/en/team/squad|title=Squad|website=Pao.gr|accessdate=29 August 2017}}</ref>\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=1|nat=Greece|name=[[Sokratis Dioudis]]|pos=GK|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=2|nat=Sweden|name=[[Mattias Johansson]]|pos=DF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=3|nat=Argentina|name=[[Emanuel Ins\u00faa]]|pos=DF|other=[[Captain (association football)|third-captain]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=4|nat=Greece|name=[[Dimitrios Kolovetsios|Dimitris Kolovetsios]]|pos=DF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=5|nat=Netherlands|name=[[Bart Schenkeveld]]|pos=DF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=7|nat=Greece|name=[[Dimitris Kolovos]]|pos=MF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=8|nat=Greece|name=[[Christos Donis]]|pos=MF|other=[[Captain (association football)|vice-captain]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=9|nat=Italy|name=[[Federico Macheda]]|pos=FW|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=10|nat=Norway|name=[[Ghayas Zahid]]|pos=MF|other=on loan from [[APOEL FC|APOEL]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=11|nat=Greece|name=[[Anastasios Chatzigiovanis|Tasos Chatzigiovanis]]|pos=MF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=12|nat=Greece|name=[[Ilias Chatzitheodoridis]]|pos=DF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=15|nat=Greece|name=[[Vasilis Xenopoulos]]|pos=GK|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=16|nat=Greece|name=[[Kostas Apostolakis]]|pos=DF|other=}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=17|nat=Denmark|name=[[Uffe Bech]]|pos=MF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=18|nat=Greece|name=[[Giannis Bouzoukis]]|pos=MF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=19|nat=Colombia|name=[[Juan Jos\u00e9 Perea]]|pos=FW|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=20|nat=Morocco|name=[[Yassin Ayoub]]|pos=MF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=21|nat=Greece|name=[[Dimitris Kourbelis]]|pos=MF|other=[[Captain (association football)|captain]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=22|nat=Hungary|name=[[Dominik Nagy]]|pos=MF|other=on loan from [[Legia Warsaw]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=26|nat=Morocco|name=[[Anuar Tuhami]]|pos=MF|other=on loan from [[Real Valladolid]]}}\n{{Fs player|no=27|nat=Greece|name=[[Konstantinos Kotsaris]]|pos=GK|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=30|nat=Portugal|name=[[Jo\u00e3o Nunes (footballer, born 1995)|Jo\u00e3o Nunes]]|pos=DF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=44|nat=Greece|name=[[Achilleas Poungouras]]|pos=DF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=57|nat=Greece|name=[[Georgios Vagiannidis|Giorgos Vagiannidis]]|pos=DF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=90|nat=Spain|name=[[Carlitos (footballer, born 1990)|Carlitos]]|pos=FW|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=99|nat=Greece|name=[[Argyris Kampetsis]]|pos=FW|other=}}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n===Out on loan===\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=24|nat=Greece|name=[[Theofanis Mavrommatis|Fanis Mavrommatis]]|pos=DF|other=at [[S\u00f8nderjyskE Fodbold|S\u00f8nderjyskE]] until 30 June 2020}}\n{{Fs player|no=\u2014|nat=Albania|name=Adriano Skenderaj|pos=MF|other=at [[Ethnikos Piraeus F.C.|Ethnikos Piraeus]] until 30 June 2020}}\n{{Fs player|no=17|nat=Greece|name=[[Dimitris Emmanouilidis]]|pos=MF|other=at [[Panionios F.C.|Panionios]] until 30 June 2020}}\n{{Fs player|no=6|nat=Spain|name=[[Fausto Tienza]]|pos=MF|other=at [[Gimn\u00e0stic de Tarragona|Gimn\u00e0stic]] until 30 June 2020}}\n{{Fs player|no=19|nat=Greece|name=[[Thanasis Dimitroulas]]|pos=DF|other=at [[Thesprotos F.C.|Thesprotos]] until 30 June 2020}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=14|nat=FRA|name=[[Yohan Mollo]]|pos=FW|other=at [[US Orl\u00e9ans|Orl\u00e9ans]] until 30 June 2020}}\n{{Fs player|no=29|nat=Netherlands|name=[[Mark Sifneos]]|pos=FW|other=at [[Apollon Larissa F.C.|Apollon Larissa]] until 30 June 2020}}\n{{Fs player|no=20|nat=Greece|name=[[Nikos Vergos]]|pos=FW|other=at [[H\u00e9rcules CF|H\u00e9rcules]] until 30 June 2020}}\n{{Fs player|no=31|nat=Albania|name=Kristo Shehu|pos=FW|other=at [[Bologna F.C. 1909|Bologna]] until 30 June 2020}}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n===Reserve squad===\n*Players of the U19 squad with professional contract\n{{Fs start}}\n{{Fs player|no=71|nat=Greece|name=[[Nikos Christogeorgos]]|pos=GK|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=47|nat=Greece|name=[[Vasilis Zagaritis]]|pos=DF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=53|nat=Greece|name=Aleksandro Sadikaj|pos=DF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=38|nat=Greece|name=Dimitris Karagiannnis|pos=DF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=39|nat=Greece|name=Ilias Iliadis|pos=MF|other=}}\n{{Fs mid}}\n{{Fs player|no=56|nat=Greece|name=Pavlos Mavroudis|pos=MF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=37|nat=Greece|name=[[Andreas Athanasakopoulos]]|pos=MF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=55|nat=Greece|name=[[Sotiris Alexandropoulos]]|pos=MF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=58|nat=Greece|name=[[Dimitris Serpezis]]|pos=MF|other=}}\n{{Fs player|no=54|nat=Greece|name=Spyros Tzavidas|pos=FW|other=}}\n{{Fs end}}\n\n===Retired Numbers===\n'''13''' \u2013 \u0399n honour of [[Gate 13]]\n\n== Former players ==\n{{see also|List of Panathinaikos F.C. players}}\n\n==Contribution to the Greek national team==\n[[File:Giorgos Kalafatis greek national team 1919.jpg|thumb|110px|Kalafatis with the [[Greece national football team|national colours]] (1919)]]\n\nOverall, Panathinaikos has a significant contribution to the [[Greece national football team|Greek national football team]]. [[Giorgos Kalafatis]], the founder of Panathinaikos, was the elector and member of the Greek national team that participated in the [[Inter-Allied Games]] in [[Paris]], while later he was also a player/manager for Greece in the [[Football at the 1920 Summer Olympics|1920 Olympic Games]] in [[Antwerp]]. During the next decades, Panathinaikos highlighted some of the best Greek players in the history of Greek football, who contributed also to the national team ([[Antonis Migiakis|Migiakis]], [[Kostas Linoxilakis|Linoxilakis]], [[Takis Loukanidis|Loukanidis]], [[Mimis Domazos|Domazos]], [[Antonis Antoniadis|Antoniadis]], [[Anthimos Kapsis|Kapsis]], [[Takis Ikonomopoulos|Ikonomopoulos]], [[Dimitris Saravakos|Saravakos]] etc.). Six Panathinaikos players were members of the first appearance of the national team in a [[FIFA World Cup|World Cup]] in 1994 ([[Dimitris Saravakos|Saravakos]], [[Thanasis Kolitsidakis|Kolitsidakis]], [[Stratos Apostolakis|Apostolakis]], [[Ioannis Kalitzakis|Kalitzakis]], [[Nikos Nioplias|Nioplias]], [[Spiros Marangos|Marangos]]).\n\nSix players of the club were part of the golden team of 2004 that won the [[UEFA Euro 2004]] and two more were ex-members of the club ([[Giorgos Karagounis]], [[Takis Fyssas]]).\n\n* [[UEFA Euro 2004 squads#Group A|UEFA Euro 2004]] (6): [[Giourkas Seitaridis]], [[Antonis Nikopolidis]], [[Kostas Chalkias]], [[Angelos Basinas]], [[Giannis Goumas]], [[Dimitris Papadopoulos (footballer)|Dimitris Papadopoulos]].\n\n==Personnel==\n===Management===\n{{See also|List of Panathinaikos F.C. presidents}}\n{{Fb cs header}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=y  |p=Ownership          |s= {{flagicon|GRE}} [[Giannis Alafouzos]] (44.24%)<br>{{flagicon|GRE}}{{flagicon|CYP}} [[#Financial information|Sortivo International Ltd]] (42.76%)}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=   |p=President & CEO    |s= {{flagicon|GRE}} Manos Mavrokoukoulakis}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=y  |p=Vice-President     |s= {{flagicon|GRE}} Leonidas Mpoutsikaris}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=   |p=Vice-President     |s={{flagicon|GRE}} Giannis Panagiotidis}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=   |p=Board Member       |s={{flagicon|GRE}} [[Giannis Alafouzos]]}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=y  |p=Board Member       |s={{flagicon|GRE}} Giorgos Mathiopoulos}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=y  |p=Board Member       |s={{flagicon|GRE}} Panagiotis Mpompis}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=   |p=Board Member       |s={{flagicon|GRE}} Pantelis Anastasopoulos}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=y  |p=Legal Department   |s={{flagicon|GRE}} Athena Balomenou}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=   |p=Media Department   |s={{flagicon|GRE}} Stamatis Garris}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=y  |p=Football Administrative \u039ffficer |s= {{flagicon|GRE}} Kostas Konstantos}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=y  |p=Football Department Coordinator  |s={{flagicon|GRE}} [[Dimitris Saravakos]]}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=y  |p=Technical Director  |s={{flagicon|ESP}} [[Xavi Roca]]}}\n|}\n\n===Technical staff===\n{{See also|List of Panathinaikos F.C. managers}}\n{{Fb cs header}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=   |p=Head Coach         |s= {{flagicon|GRE}} [[Giorgos Donis]]}}\n{{Fb cs staff |bg=   |